      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:18:2",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ ( عليه السلام ) عَنْ رَجُلٍ قَتَلَ أُمَّهُ قَالَ يُقْتَلُ بِهَا صَاغِراً وَ لَا أَظُنُّ قَتْلَهُ كَفَّارَةً لَهُ وَ لَا يَرِثُهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Ibn Raib, from Abu Umeyda who said, ",
          "‘I asked Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> about a man who killed his mother. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He would be killed due to it, belittled, and I<sup>asws</sup> do not think killing him would be an expiation for him, and he would not inherit her’."
        ]
      }
    },
